        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 15 at 6:18PM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 617 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Table Mountain, or 20 miles southwest of Bowman, moving northeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mud Buttes and Bowman Haley Dam.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
